title: The Testament
author: Charlieseeese
pages:
#- The BennyZ Testament§0
§0
§0 In the First Age, in the first battle, when the shadows first lengthened, one stood. Burned by the embers of Hallow, his soul blistered by the fires of Laconia and tainted beyond ascension, he chose the path of perpetual PVP.
#- In his ravenous hatred he found no peace; and with boiling blood he scoured the Holy Jaded Empire seeking vengeance against the natoids who had wronged him. He wore the crown of the PvPers, and those that tasted the bite of his sword named him...§0

#- .. The NATO Slayer.§0
§0  Tempered by the fires of Hell, his diamond will remained steadfast through the passage that preys upon the weak. For he alone was the NATO Walker, the Unchained Predator, who sought retribution in all quarters, dark and light, fire..
#- and ice, in the beginning and the end, and he hunted the slaves of NATO with barbarous cruelty, for he passed through the divide as none but natoid had before.§0
§0 And in his conquest against the blackened souls of the doomed, his prowess was shown. In his..
#- crusade, MIR bestowed upon him terrible power and speed, and with his might he crushed the obsidian pillars of Ransakistan. He set forth without pity upon the beasts of NATO. Unbreakable, incorruptible, unyielding, the NATO slayer, sought to end the
#- the dominion of the dark realm.§0
§0 The age of his reckoning was uncounted. The scribes carved his name deep in the tablets of NATO for eons, and each battle etched terror into the hearts of the natoids. They knew he would come, as he always had, as he..
#- always will, to feast upon the blood of the wicked. For he alone could draw strength from his fallen foes, and ever his power grew, swift and unrelenting.§0
§0 None could stand before the horde but the NATO Slayer. Despair spread before him like a plague, 
#- striking fear into the basement-dwellers, driving them to deeper and darker pits. But from the depths of the abyss rose Adderall Crew, champions mightier than all who had come before. The Titans, of immeasurable power and ferocity. They strode
#- upon the plain and faced the NATO Slayer, and a mighty battle was fought on the desolate plains. The Titans fought with the fury of the countless that had fallen at the NATO Slayer's hand, but there fell the Titans, and in his defeat the
#- NATO horde were routed.§0
§0  And in his terrible rancor between nations and through time, the NATO Walker found the wretch who shall not be named, but in his heresy was loyal to his evil cause. The wretch adorned the NATO Slayer in mighty Prot4 UB3 armor
#- wrought in the forges of Laconia, impenetrable and unyielding. With sword and shield of adamantine strength, the NATO Slayer set to banishing all that were left unbroken by his savagery to the End. Yet as the mighty Titans fell and dread engulfed the
#- armies of NATO, the natoid priests of Pinkerton laid a trap to capture this scourge of NATO. Insatiable, even by the vanquishing of the Great One, the NATO Walker sought prey in the tombs of Pinkerton. The priest brought down the obsidian upon the NATO
#- Slayer, and in his defeat entombed him in the cursed sarcophagus. The mark of the NATO Slayer was burned upon his obsidian crypt, a warning to all of NATO that the terror within must never be freed. There he lies still, and ever more, in silent suffering.
#- 